01:08:08.880 --> 01:08:10.500
one of the things that we've talked

01:08:10.500 --> 01:08:14.570
about as a really important
philosophical question is that --

01:08:14.570 --> 01:08:17.220
is the question of how
does a language survive?

01:08:17.220 --> 01:08:20.700
And a language survives,
weirdly enough,

01:08:20.700 --> 01:08:23.440
through the process of translation.

01:08:23.440 --> 01:08:26.820
Translation actually
allows a language to survive

01:08:26.820 --> 01:08:31.010
because if the culture
produces a work --

01:08:31.010 --> 01:08:32.310
I mean, this is something

01:08:32.310 --> 01:08:37.520
that I think Ngugi wa Thiong'o
was always arguing about, Gikuyu.

01:08:37.520 --> 01:08:39.760
In 1986, when I met
