he was no longer going to write

01:08:43.770 --> 01:08:46.550
in English and everything he was
going to write was going to be

01:08:46.550 --> 01:08:49.720
in Gikuyu and it's
going to be translated.

01:08:49.720 --> 01:08:52.850
At the time, Ngugi was clear
about this and felt this is going

01:08:52.850 --> 01:08:54.240
to be important and so on.

01:08:54.240 --> 01:08:56.990
Well, it became very clear
quickly to him and to all of us

01:08:56.990 --> 01:09:00.870
that if somebody didn't
get that work translated,

01:09:00.870 --> 01:09:05.060
then this project was going
to suffer at some point,

01:09:05.060 --> 01:09:07.990
and Ngugi recognized that.

01:09:07.990 --> 01:09:12.640
And so, his last novels, whether
it's Matigari and Devil --

01:09:12.640 --> 01:09:16.810
the lastest one, the crow
one, I forget the name of it,

01:09:16.810 --> 01:09:19.940
all were written originally
in Gikuyu and then translated.

01:09:19.940 --> 01:09:23.670
But you can see that when he
started his first set of books,

01:09:23.670 --> 01:09:26.690
which were written in English,
were published at a rapid pace.

01:09:26.690 --> 01:09:33.220
As soon as he took on this new
mandate, publication slowed down.

01:09:33.220 --> 01:09:35.530
Right? And it's not
